cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SI

This paper proposes a novel approach for preserving topological structures in latent representations of autoencoders using persistent homology, a technique from topological data analysis. The paper focuses on the application of this approach to image data sets, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the computer science sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and social and information networks (cs.SI). Among these, cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely categories, as the paper deals with learning representations of image data sets.
